The paper deals with face sketch synthesis, which is a problem in computer vision and image processing. The proposed method involves random sampling and locality constraint, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves optimization and computational complexity, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of public face sketch databases and evaluation metrics suggests relevance to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
